{'problem_id': 'op_000066', 'moved_to': 'archived', 'target_row': {'id': 'op_000066', 'stmt': 'For any Γ A Δ s, if residualAtomicState Γ A = some (Δ, s), then the set of residual-graph states reachable from (Δ, s) is finite.', 'src': 'expand', 'mode': 'expand_candidate', 'summary_delta': 'Once residual states are known to stay within subformulas of the original sequent, a genuine theory-level consequence is finiteness of the reachable region. That is a reusable metatheorem for recognition and decidability, and it advances the current bottleneck more directly than additional witness-packaging lemmas.', 'source_kind': 'expand_candidate', 'generated_from_source_id': 'op_000061', 'generated_from_source_kind': 'open_problem', 'priority': 'high', 'priority_rationale': 'This directly turns the current reachable-state subformula invariant into reachable-region finiteness, which would rewrite the theory summary and unlock finite recognition.', 'failure_count': 2, 'parent_problem_ids': []}, 'solved_row': None, 'counterexample_row': None, 'duplicate_stmt_rows_removed': [], 'current_iteration': 5, 'picked_problem_id': 'op_000066', 'picked_problem_priority': 'high', 'result': 'proof', 'verify_success': False, 'verify_error_excerpt': "AutomatedTheoryConstruction/Scratch.loop.lean:45:6: warning: try 'simp' instead of 'simpa'", 'original_stmt': 'For any Γ A Δ s, if residualAtomicState Γ A = some (Δ, s), then the set of residual-graph states reachable from (Δ, s) is finite.', 'statement_prelude_code': '', 'formalized_stmt': '∀ (Γ Δ : List Tp) (A : Tp) (s : String),\n  residualAtomicState Γ A = some (Δ, s) →\n  Set.Finite { q : AtomicResidualState | Relation.ReflTransGen AtomicResidualGraphStep (Δ, s) q }', 'prelude_code': 'lemma subformula_set_finite (C : Tp) : Set.Finite {B : Tp | Subformula B C} := by\n  induction C with\n  | atom s =>\n      refine (Set.finite_singleton (# s)).subset ?_\n      intro B hB\n      cases hB\n      simp\n  | ldiv A B ihA ihB =>\n      refine ((ihA.union ihB).union (Set.finite_singleton (A ⧹ B))).subset ?_\n      intro X hX\n      cases hX with\n      | refl =>\n          simp\n      | ldiv_left h =>\n          simp [h]\n      | ldiv_right h =>\n          simp [h]\n  | rdiv A B ihA ihB =>\n      refine ((ihA.union ihB).union (Set.finite_singleton (A ⧸ B))).subset ?_\n      intro X hX\n      cases hX with\n      | refl =>\n          simp\n      | rdiv_left h =>\n          simp [h]\n      | rdiv_right h =>\n          simp [h]\n\nlemma subformula_support_finite (src : List Tp) :\n    Set.Finite {B : Tp | ∃ C ∈ src, Subformula B C} := by\n  induction src with\n  | nil =>\n      simpa using (Set.finite_empty : Set.Finite (∅ : Set Tp))\n  | cons C src ih =>\n      rw [show ({B : Tp | ∃ D ∈ C :: src, Subformula B D} : Set Tp) =\n          {B : Tp | Subformula B C} ∪ {B : Tp | ∃ D ∈ src, Subformula B D} by\n        ext B\n        simp]\n      exact (subformula_set_finite C).union ih\n\nlemma finite_lists_bounded_of_finite {α : Type*} {S : Set α} (hS : S.Finite) :\n    ∀ N : Nat,\n      Set.Finite {l : List α | l.length ≤ N ∧ ∀ a ∈ l, a ∈ S} := by\n  intro N\n  induction N with\n  | zero =>\n      refine (Set.finite_singleton ([] : List α)).subset ?_\n      intro l hl\n      cases l with\n      | nil =>\n          simp\n      | cons a tl =>\n          simp at hl\n  | succ N ih =>\n      let T : Set (List α) := {l | l.length ≤ N ∧ ∀ a ∈ l, a ∈ S}\n      have hT : T.Finite := ih\n      refine ((Set.finite_singleton ([] : List α)).union\n        (Set.Finite.image (fun p : α × List α => p.1 :: p.2) (hS.prod hT))).subset ?_\n      intro l hl\n      cases l with\n      | nil =>\n          simp\n      | cons a tl =>\n          right\n          refine ⟨(a, tl), ?_, rfl⟩\n          constructor\n          · exact hl.2 a (by simp)\n          · change tl.length ≤ N ∧ ∀ b ∈ tl, b ∈ S\n            constructor\n            · simpa using hl.1\n            · intro b hb\n              exact hl.2 b (by simp [hb])\n\nlemma list_length_le_list_degree : ∀ Γ : List Tp, Γ.length ≤ list_degree Γ\n  | [] => by\n      simp [list_degree]\n  | A :: Γ => by\n      have hA : 1 ≤ tp_degree A := by\n        cases A <;> simp [tp_degree]\n      have hΓ : Γ.length ≤ list_degree Γ := list_length_le_list_degree Γ\n      calc\n        (A :: Γ).length = 1 + Γ.length := by simp\n        _ ≤ tp_degree A + list_degree Γ := Nat.add_le_add hA hΓ\n        _ = list_degree (A :: Γ) := by simp [list_degree]\n\nlemma atomicResidualGraphStep_degree_lt {p q : AtomicResidualState}\n    (h : AtomicResidualGraphStep p q) :\n    list_degree q.1 < list_degree p.1 := by\n  cases h with\n  | rdiv Γ L Δ Λ A B s hc harg =>\n      have hΓ : Γ = L ++ [B ⧸ A] ++ Δ ++ Λ := by\n        symm\n        simpa using (candidates_list_degree (Γ := Γ) (c := Cand.rdiv L B A Δ Λ) hc)\n      rw [hΓ]\n      simp [list_degree_traversible, List.append_assoc, list_degree, tp_degree]\n      omega\n  | ldiv Γ Γ₁ Δ R A B s hc harg =>\n      have hΓ : Γ = Γ₁ ++ Δ ++ [A ⧹ B] ++ R := by\n        symm\n        simpa using (candidates_list_degree (Γ := Γ) (c := Cand.ldiv Γ₁ Δ A B R) hc)\n      rw [hΓ]\n      simp [list_degree_traversible, List.append_assoc, list_degree, tp_degree]\n      omega\n\nlemma residual_reachable_degree_le {p q : AtomicResidualState}\n    (h : Relation.ReflTransGen AtomicResidualGraphStep p q) :\n    list_degree q.1 ≤ list_degree p.1 := by\n  induction h with\n  | refl =>\n      exact le_rfl\n  | tail hreach hstep ih =>\n      exact le_trans (atomicResidualGraphStep_degree_lt hstep).le ih', 'prover_statement_result': 'ok', 'prover_attempts_used': 1, 'priority_refresh_ran': True, 'priority_refresh_error': '', 'expand_candidates': [], 'stored_expand_rows': [], 'promoted_expand_rows': [], 'batch_generator_added_problem_rows': [], 'batch_generator_error': '', 'pending_expand_candidate_count': 1, 'archived_problem_count': 17, 'active_open_problem_count': 1, 'iteration': 5}
